#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:3
msgid "Administrative interfaces for nfsd"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:5
msgid ""
"Note that normally these interfaces are used only by the utilities in nfs-"
"utils."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:8
msgid ""
"nfsd is controlled mainly by pseudofiles under the \"nfsd\" filesystem, "
"which is normally mounted at /proc/fs/nfsd/."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:11
msgid ""
"The server is always started by the first write of a nonzero value to nfsd/"
"threads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:14
msgid ""
"Before doing that, NFSD can be told which sockets to listen on by writing to "
"nfsd/portlist; that write may be:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:17
msgid ""
"an ascii-encoded file descriptor, which should refer to a bound (and "
"listening, for tcp) socket, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:19
msgid ""
"\"transportname port\", where transportname is currently either \"udp\", "
"\"tcp\", or \"rdma\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:22
msgid ""
"If nfsd is started without doing any of these, then it will create one udp "
"and one tcp listener at port 2049 (see nfsd_init_socks)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:25
msgid ""
"On startup, nfsd and lockd grace periods start. nfsd is shut down by a write "
"of 0 to nfsd/threads.  All locks and state are thrown away at that point."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:28
msgid ""
"Between startup and shutdown, the number of threads may be adjusted up or "
"down by additional writes to nfsd/threads or by writes to nfsd/pool_threads."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:32
msgid ""
"For more detail about files under nfsd/ and what they control, see fs/nfsd/"
"nfsctl.c; most of them have detailed comments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:36
msgid "Implementation notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/nfs/nfsd-admin-interfaces.rst:38
msgid ""
"Note that the rpc server requires the caller to serialize addition and "
"removal of listening sockets, and startup and shutdown of the server. For "
"nfsd this is done using nfsd_mutex."
msgstr ""
